review_blob: Who watchout! Not your typical Amber. I would have rated this lower if the brewer didnt warn me ahead of time. What a nice twist on a traditional beer. Plesantly suprised!
beer_name: Geneva Lake Cedar Point Amber Ale

review_blob: Loved this and I dont like dark beers! Really light compared to most stouts!
beer_name: Geneva Lake Black Point Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Great light taste! A good pick for thier new lightest beer line up. Another plus on the drinkable scale.
Really hope they bring this one back because it was so good! So light -- such a surprise when you find out how strong it is!
Couldnt believe this! Loved it more than their regular IPA! You can tell that its made with local honey and goes down so smooth!
I actually saw the headbrewer make this beer. It turned out so nice! Not super pumpkiny like some of the main stream Pumpkin Ales out there. It was perfect!
The perfect summer beer. Refreshing and light. Everyone can like this beer.
Perfect Every day sitting on the dock drinking beer. One everyone may like. Way better than Spotted Cow

IPA lovers unite!! Best IPA ever!!!! Made with 8 different types of hops its mellow on the pallet and not too in your face! Beautiful orange/yellowy color. Amazing fresh citrus smell ANC grape fruit taste. No bad taste in your mouth like most ipas!
